    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "subjective experience is just a way to distract ourselves from the fact that we're just biological accidents. it feels like i'm just fighting a losing battle against the nothingness every single day. it's exhausting to pretend that existing is worth the effort when the end result is always the same. if the void is what's actually real, then why is it considered \"wrong\" to want to just be part of it instead of fighting it?",
